    "updated_at": "2015-02-20T13:31:36Z",
    "body": "Note that the function does not build a list, but rather generates results lazily, therefore yes, sending result of `fs::read_dir` into a thread is not safe. \n\nWrap the iterator into `Arc<Mutex<>>` or build a list before sending it to the thread pool with `fs::read_dir(dir).collect<Vec<_>>()`.\n",
